AudioCodes Drops Most Since 2000 on Lower Revenue Forecast

-- B y   T a l   B a r a k   H a r i f
-- 
2011-10-03T21:30:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-03/audiocodes-drops-most-since-2008-on-lower-revenue-forecast-1-.html
AudioCodes Ltd. (AUDC) , a maker of
technology to enable internet phone calls, fell the most in more
than a decade after cutting its annual revenue outlook.  Shares of the Lod, Israel-based company sank 27 percent to
$2.29 on the Nasdaq Stock Market by 4 p.m. in  New York , the most
since December 2000. AudioCodesâ€™ Tel Aviv stock lost 7.9 percent
to 10.58 shekels, the equivalent of $2.81.  AudioCodes expects full-year revenue of $155 million to
$162 million, according to a statement distributed by Globe
Newswire today. The company previously forecast revenue of as
much as $174 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
